<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-17267] New group coordinator can return REQUEST_TIMED_OUT for OFFSET_FETCHes</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-17267</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Under some circumstances, the new group coordinator can return &lt;tt&gt;REQUEST_TIMED_OUT&lt;/tt&gt; errors in response to &lt;tt&gt;OFFSET_FETCH&lt;/tt&gt; requests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the client (ConsumerCoordinator) does not handle this error code and treats it as non-retryable. For compatibility with older clients, we can map &lt;tt&gt;REQUEST_TIMED_OUT&lt;/tt&gt; to &lt;tt&gt;NOT_COORDINATOR&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Similar to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-16386&quot; title=&quot;NETWORK_EXCEPTIONs from transaction verification are not translated&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;KAFKA-16386&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;KAFKA-16386&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
